                <h1>Exploring the Roots of Jiu Jitsu: Its Origins and Evolution</h1>
                <p>Jiu Jitsu originated in Japan during the late 19th century as a form of unarmed combat, focusing on grappling techniques. It was developed by the samurai as a method of self-defense when unarmed. The martial art was later adapted and spread to Brazil, where it evolved into Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, emphasizing ground fighting and submission techniques.</p>
